# Ory Hydra v2.3.0 — SQLite-enabled binary (CGO build with libsqlite3).
# File: hydra_2.3.0-linux_sqlite_64bit.tar.gz
# Source: https://github.com/ory/hydra/releases/download/v2.3.0/checksums.txt
# Verified: 2026-04-20
#
# WHY THE SQLITE VARIANT (not the default linux_64bit build):
# Ory ships two Linux amd64 tarballs per release — the default is
# compiled WITHOUT SQLite support (MySQL/Postgres/CockroachDB only).
# A SQLite-flavoured CGO build lives behind the `-sqlite_64bit` suffix.
# Our DSN is sqlite:///var/lib/jabali-hydra/db.sqlite3 (ADR-0036
# amendment), so the default binary errors out at migrate time with
# "SQLite support was not built into the binary. Binary archives
# indicate SQLite support by appending the -sqlite suffix".
#
# Plan m16-hydra-oauth.md §8 pinned "v2.4.x" as the target at blueprint
# time; v2.3.0 is the latest stable 2.x (Ory jumped straight to
# calendar-versioned v25.x/v26.x after — no v2.4 exists). We stay on
# the last semver-tagged self-hosted line until we have a reason to
# jump. Bump the version + this checksum + the install.sh URL together;
# Hydra's migrations are idempotent and safe to re-run on upgrade.
9a05dca5076427d18f6a57bc58542c75989a0e37a605c85962ffc8a7cc3ba707  hydra_2.3.0-linux_sqlite_64bit.tar.gz
